net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.composite.editor

Class FileEntityValueRenderer

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.composite.editor.FileEntityValueRenderer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Component>, net.proteusframework.core.locale.LocaleContextSource, Component, ValueRenderer<net.proteusframework.data.filesystem.FileEntity>, ListCellRenderer, TableCellRenderer, TreeCellRenderer

    @Configurable(preConstruction=true)
public class FileEntityValueRenderer
extends ComponentImpl
implements TreeCellRenderer, ValueRenderer<net.proteusframework.data.filesystem.FileEntity>
    A component that presents a clickable widget that opens a Link for a FileEntity. The text value is displayed to the user. If no text value is set then the URI is displayed.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@proteus.co)

        public net.proteusframework.core.html.Element getHTMLElement()
        Description copied from interface: Component
        Get the top level elements this component will output in its current state. This should not included the entire content model.

        For example, if your code outputs the following, <p><span><b></b></span></p>, then you should only return one element that is a "p"; NOT "p, span, b".

        All configuration elements should be nested within this top element, or other arrangements should be made with the inner keeper.
